Key Match Events: Daulton Varsho and Spencer Horwitz each hit two-run homers in a seven-run first inning as the Blue Jays routed the Twins 15-0.
The Blue Jays hit three two-run homers in the game.
José Berríos tossed six shutout innings as the Blue Jays routed the Twins 15-0.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Blue Jays' 15-0 victory was their largest margin of victory this season.
The Twins were shut out for the 10th time this season.
The game was played at Target Field in Minneapolis, Minnesota, in front of a crowd of 30,517.
